Does anyone know if you can output two variables to a choice value `E.g. choices="{{ layout }} ~ {{ sections }}"` -

```{% for section in sections|split(',', widget_data.sections_field.value) %}
		{% choice "layout_field" label="Layout for block (Content)", value="Content", choices="{{ layout }}", export_to_template_context=True, unique_in_loop=True %}
{% endfor %}```

Also want to add a number to each loop here too `E.g. {% if widget.value == "Banner ~ {{ loop.index }}" %}

```{% for widget in widget_data %}
			{% if loop.index0 &lt;= widget_data.sections_field.value %}
          {% if widget.value == "Banner" %}```

I want to add the loop number to the end of any choice made then match against a subsequent `widget.value`
